                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/hist-201" class="program-course-title">
              HIST 201 Modern African History (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-27388" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      History              : While covering the general political history of Africa in the twentieth century, this course also explores such themes as health and disease, gender, and urbanization.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Jon Soske (Winter)                  </p>

    
